Two suspects aged 38 and 53 were arrested recently during an operation led by the eThekwini Outer South cluster and uMlazi police officers.  They face fraud and possession of stolen property charges. Police spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker, said, “The 38-year-old suspect was arrested at the offices of the Department of Home Affairs after she attempted to apply for two birth certificates while utilizing fraudulent proof of birth cards from a hospital. She was detained at the uMlazi police station. “Following further investigation, police proceeded to Folweni where a 53-year-old suspect was arrested. “The suspect was arrested after police seized 39 birth certificates, 37 identity document copies, a hospital stamp, two school stamps, an education department circuit stamp, two identity documents and proof of birth cards. They appeared in the uMlazi Magistrates Court.” The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Julia commended  police officers for their diligent investigations.“The fraudulent activities are robbing government of a lot of money and depriving underprivileged community members of their social grants,” he said.